{"talk":{"id":1857,"name":"Holly Morris: Why stay in Chernobyl? Because it's home.","description":"Chernobyl was the site of the world's worst nuclear accident and, for the past 27 years, the area around the plant has been known as the Exclusion Zone. And yet, a community of about 200 people live there -- almost all of them elderly women. These proud grandmas defied orders to relocate because their connection to their homeland and to their community are \"forces that rival even radiation.\"","slug":"holly_morris_why_stay_in_chernobyl_because_it_s_home","recorded_at":"2013-06-12 00:00:00","published_at":"2013-10-31 14:58:15","updated_at":"2021-04-09 19:31:11","viewed_count":1134344,"emailed_count":136,"event":{"id":241,"name":"TEDGlobal 2013"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/0a171bdca14ddd15b93272a730c83719a1ac5c53_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/0a171bdca14ddd15b93272a730c83719a1ac5c53_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/0a171bdca14ddd15b93272a730c83719a1ac5c53_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"1600x1200","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/0a171bdca14ddd15b93272a730c83719a1ac5c53_1600x1200.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":false,"media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/HollyMorris_2013G-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":4369904,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/HollyMorris_2013G-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":12051869,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/HollyMorris_2013G-320k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":21418474,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"450k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/HollyMorris_2013G-450k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":30219081